# Core Architecture

## Folder map (real)
- `src/app/` — Next.js App Router (pages + `api/` routes, including `api/experimental/fetch`).
- `src/components/legacy-ui/` — active UI (misnamed "legacy"); `src/components/ui/` — generic widgets.
- `src/components/Experimental/` — **MVP** isolated weather engine (types, data/, Coverage/, Algorithms/, Components/). Does NOT modify V1.
- `src/core/` — orchestration (`forecastCore.js`). `src/services/` — client data access. `src/lib/` — `fetchMeteoData.js` (I/O). `src/store/` — Zustand. `src/utils/` — pure helpers. `src/types/`.
- `traitement/` — per-variable processing (server, Node fs/path). `shared/` — pure stat/weather algorithms. `config/` — per-variable JSON.
- `legacy/`, `public/test-algo/`, `docs/` — archives & docs (not app code).

## Layering (keep strict)
- UI never reaches data I/O directly: UI → `services/` → `api/` route → `core/` → `traitement/` → `shared/`.
- `shared/*` algorithms stay PURE (no I/O, no config read) → testable.
- `traitement/*` should receive data injected rather than re-calling `fetchMeteoData` (target; see backlog A5).

## File size
- Target ≤ 200 lines; split beyond. Exception: static data tables / icon maps.

## DRY & single source of truth
- If a pattern appears twice, extract it. Constants, model lists, thresholds live in ONE place — never hardcode URLs/magic values inline (model list is duplicated in `fetchMeteoData` URL and JSON configs — avoid widening this).

## Naming
- Components `PascalCase`; hooks `useThing`; vars/functions `camelCase`; true constants `UPPER_SNAKE_CASE`. Booleans read as predicates (`isReady`, `hasItems`).
